BLUETONGUE, RUMINANTS - BOSNIA & HERZEGOVINA, BULGARIA
**************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 5 Sept 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Office International des Epizooties [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/en_urgences.htm>

[1]
BULGARIA
(Date of previous reported outbreak: October 2001).
Information dated 2 Sep 2002 was received on 3 Sep 2002 from Dr Nikola T
Belev, Delegate of Bulgaria to the OIE:
As of the report date, 3 laboratory diagnosed (competition ELISA) outbreaks
of bluetongue have been reported in Smolian region (south of the country).
The animal health incident was first detected on 30 Aug 2002 (estimated
date of first infection: 30 Aug 2002).
The affected population consists of cattle and goats: 13 cases among 700
susceptible.
Origin of infection: possible transborder penetration of culicoides from
the south.
Control measures:
- control of arthropods;
- control programme covering the whole country
- quarantine and movement control inside the country
- treatment
- screening
- vaccination prohibited
******
[2]

BOSNIA AND HERZEGOVINA
(Disease never previously reported)
Information dated 3 Sep 2002 received on 3 Sep 2002 from Prof Dr Marko
Tadic, Director of State Veterinary Administration of Bosnia and Herzegovina:
Animal health incident detected: 27 Aug 2002; estimated date of first
infection: 2 Aug 2002.
The affected population consists of cattle, sheep, and goats. A total of
169 cases have been reported in 19 outbreaks.
Geographical locations: municipalities of Kalesija, Sapno, Rudo, Zvornik,
Milici, Srebrenica, Sekovici, Vlasenica, Bratunac, Osmaci, Visegrad,
Kalinovik, Srbinje, Pale, and Trebinje.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory (ELISA)
The source of agent/origin of infection are under investigation.
Mode of spread: culicoides.
Control measures:
- control of arthropods;
- quarantine and movement control inside the country;
- modified stamping-out policy;
- screening.
--
